Religious leaders have raised concerns about what they call unfair treatment by government under level 1 lockdown regulations. Churches are now allowed to host 100 congregants indoors and 200 outside when they hold services. #eNCA​ Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Religious leaders have raised concerns about what they call unfair treatment by government under level 1 lockdown regulations. Churches are now allowed to host 100 congregants indoors and 200 outside when they hold services. READ: Churches resume services But, some congregations believe government should prescribe capacity in percentages and not employ a one size fits all method. For more, watch the video above for more on this story More congregants are returning to church today. Under Level One Lockdown, gatherings are allowed but limited to 100 people indoors and 250 outdoors. eNCA's @LindokuhlXulu1 spoke to a family at a church in Midrand. #DStv403 #eNCA pic.twitter.com/YMMVmbneP3